article.description: — Keegan Records had a career-high 25 points as Colgate ended its seven-game road losing streak, beating Navy 69-50 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Records scores 25 to lead Colgate past Navy 69-50
article.linkText: Records scores 25 to lead Colgate past Navy 69-50
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- — Keegan Records had a career-high 25 points as Colgate ended its seven-game road losing streak, beating Navy 69-50 on Thursday night. Records made 11 of 13 shots. He added seven rebounds. Nelly Cummings had 16 points for Colgate (6-10, 2-1 Patriot League). Jack Ferguson added seven rebounds. Navy scored 24 first-half points, a season low for the team. Tyler Nelson had 9 points for the Midshipmen (11-5, 4-1), whose four-game win streak came to an end. Sean Yoder also had 9 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
